lenders.name: Kate
lenders.loan_because: ...why not?  I'm a follower of Jesus, and I think of all of the world's resources (money and food, sure, but also encouragement, inspiration, family, etc...) as "God's Economy".  As I share what I have, I am provided with what I need, too.  My friend, an artist, helped me redecorate my apartment because it was a task that rendered me incompetent.  For her, it took about ten minutes to get some ideas, AND she enjoyed it.  Later, I cooked for her, something I love to do and do so [fairly] effortlessly; the meal blew her away.  We each got something we needed (or wanted) but far more efficiently and joyously than had we tried to get those things on our own.  With lending, it is easy for me to loan someone $50 to start a business, whereas starting my own business -something I'd love to do one day- isn't a reality for me right now.  Here, I get the benefit of knowing I helped someone with their dream, and it costs me, comparatively, nothing.  I am so glad to be able to interact with individuals across the world in this way.
lenders.occupational_info: I'm currently not employed, but am eagerly waiting for my first baby to make his or her appearance.  I'm an American living temporarily in Sweden with my husband, and I spend my time studying to be a doula (a woman that physically and emotionally supports other women during birth) and doing some birth advocacy work.  Ever since I was young I've been passionate about equal rights for women, and my eyes are still getting wider as I realize how great the need is to empower women world-wide.  I hope to put more time and energy into this in the near future.

lenders.name: Doug
lenders.loan_because: Im willing to help Musicially talented people throughout the world create great music as well as give to a great cause
lenders.occupational_info:
Music for Life will be an Australian based foundation that helps young people with musical talent record their music in a professional environment without the stress of affordability as most of the production cost is waivered with support from local and international sponsors with a series of concerts held each year to raise funds to help young people get the push to get themselves out there..

Each year most of the talent in the music industry is missed because, for some it is just not an affordable option to record their music. One out of ten of the musicians in this situation are probably the next big name you hear on the radio , but getting from here to there is so hard when the only person hearing them is close friends and relatives in-between the walls of their house . Our main focus is getting the unknown musicians out there at no cost and providing them with support through various social networking channels to turn their life around and give them a positive break into a hard industry.

Just like the old days when “Elvis” walked in off the street and became “the king” we want to be able to change people’s lives forever through the power of music.

With help and donations from local and international sponsors together in one cause , we can make this foundation a reality , all we need to get moving along is the basic equipment and knowledge to go together to help form something for everyone that counts in a big way.

When everything is finalized we hope to help a broad range of people, by donating most of the proceeds of every popular recording to selected charities other than ours.

If you have anything that might be of help to us such as a studio “a mixing desk, an old guitar or two, or even knowledge how to use some modern recording equipment, we could use your help as with your support we can achieve something great that every unearthed musician needs “a chance”.
